---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { u } from "../consts";
---
<Base title="Our Standard — Grimsley Mineral Co." active="standard">
  <div class="pagehead">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="crumb"><a href={u("")}>Home</a> / Our Standard</div>
      <h1>Our Standard</h1>
      <p>A specimen is only as good as the information that comes with it. We grade and describe every piece the same way, so you always know what you are buying before it ships.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="prose">
    <ol>
      <li><b>Honest about condition.</b>We look each specimen over for chips, bruises, contacts, and repairs, and we say what we find. Natural imperfections are part of collecting, so we point them out plainly instead of hiding them in a good camera angle.</li>
      <li><b>Crystal quality over size.</b>A bigger specimen is not automatically a better one. We choose pieces for luster, color, clarity, and clean crystal form first. Size matters, but it never covers for a dull or damaged crystal.</li>
      <li><b>Documented locality.</b>Where a specimen came from is part of its value and its story. We list the locality as specifically as we can, down to the mine or region when the source is known, and we do not guess or dress it up when it is not.</li>
      <li><b>Honest treatment disclosure.</b>Some material is treated, and that is fine when it is disclosed. If a piece is heat treated, dyed, or stabilized, we say so. Most commercial citrine is heat treated amethyst, and we label it that way.</li>
      <li><b>Accurate photography.</b>Our photos show the specimen as it is, in even light, without filters that punch up color beyond real life. What you see on the screen is what arrives at your door.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <section class="learn">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sec-top"><div class="k">Field Notes</div><h2>Learn the stone</h2><p>Short reads on how a specimen is graded, what a locality tells you, and how to care for what you collect.</p></div>
      <div class="center-cta"><a class="btn btn-dark" href={u("field-notes")}>Read the field notes</a></div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
